napshot. The last-active column shows\n28: > `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM` (committer local offset) because most folders share one commit day — the time\n29: > is what orders them. The `born` column is the folder's recorded `created_at` (or first git commit\n30: > of its `spec.md`), shown at day granularity.\n31: >\n32: > **Folder numbers are NOT chronology.** Numbers (`000`–`007`, child `NNN-`) encode topical/structural\n33: > identity assigned across reorg waves. This file is the *only* surface that orders by when work happened.\n34: > Phase identity → home mapping lives in [`context-index.md`](./context-index.md); the live track map lives\n35: > in [`spec.md`](./spec.md).\n36: >\n37: > **Changelog links:** §D maps every live spec folder to its packet changelog(s). Folders with none\n38: > (docs-only, research, or work consolidated into a parent rollup) show `(none)`. Phase parents link\n39: > their `-root.md` rollup, which indexes the child phase changelogs.\n40: >\n41: > **Most recent live spec folder:** `001-peck-teachings-adoption/006-peck-verification-discipline`\n42: > **Oldest live spec folder:** `000-release-cleanup/001-public-root-readme`\n43: > **Counts:** 83 live spec folders · 0 archived (`z_archive/`).\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 0. Most recent 15 (quick answer to \"what was worked on last\")\n48: \n49: ```\n50:  1. 2026-06-10 16:13  001-peck-teachings-adoption/006-peck-verification-discipline\n51:  2. 2026-06-10 16:13  001-peck-teachings-adoption\n52:  3. 2026-06-10 16:12  008-openltm-retrieval-observability\n53:  4. 2026-06-10 14:50  009-openltm-continuity-resilience\n54:  5. 2026-06-10 14:50  007-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening/005-stale-audit-and-tool-ownership\n55:  6. 2026-06-10 14:50  007-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening\n56:  7. 2026-06-10 14:49  007-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening/004-tombstones-and-edge-promotion\n57:  8. 2026-06-10 13:39  007-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening/003-feedback-log-and-005-reframe\n58:  9. 2026-06-10 13:39  005-learning-feedback-reducers/003-causal-reducer\n59: 10. 2026-06-10 13:39  005-learning-feedback-reducers\n60: 11. 2026-06-10 13:15  007-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening/002-idempotency-and-near-duplicate\n61: 12. 2026-06-10 12:45  007-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening/001-provenance-and-audit\n62: 13. 2026-06-10 12:01  005-learning-feedback-reducers/005-env-tests-integration\n63: 14. 2026-06-10 11:48  005-learning-feedback-reducers/004-retention-reducer\n64: 15. 2026-06-10 11:12  005-learning-feedback-reducers/001-aggregator\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## A. Tracks — newest activity → oldest\n70: \n71: The eight top-level themed tracks, ordered by most recent git activity. `Born` uses `--follow` so it\n72: traces through the reorg `git mv` history to each track's true origin.\n73: \n74: | Rank | Last active | Born | Track |\n75: |------|------------------|------------|-------|\n76: | 1 | 2026-06-10 16:13 | 2026-06-02 | `001-peck-teachings-adoption/` |\n77: | 2 | 2026-06-10 16:12 | 2026-06-08 | `008-openltm-retrieval-observability/` |\n78: | 3 | 2026-06-10 14:50 | 2026-06-08 | `009-openltm-continuity-resilience/` |\n79: | 4 | 2026-06-10 14:50 | 2026-06-06 | `007-memclaw-derived-memory-hardening/` |\n80: | 5 | 2026-06-10 13:39 | 2026-05-09 | `005-learning-feedback-reducers/` |\n81: | 6 | 2026-06-10 11:00 | 2026-06-06 | `004-semantic-trigger-fallback/` |\n82: | 7 | 2026-06-10 09:15 | 2026-06-06 | `003-memory-index-causal-lifecycle/` |\n83: | 8 | 2026-06-10 08:24 | 2026-06-06 | `006-gem-team-adoption/` |\n84: | 9 | 2026-06-10 08:03 | 2026-06-06 | `010-mcp-to-cli-tool-transition/` |\n85: | 10 | 2026-06-10 07:38 | 2026-05-11 | `002-memory-write-safety/` |\n86: | 11 | 2026-05-31 09:56 | 2026-06-10 | `000-release-cleanup/` |\n87: | 12 | ??????????      | 2026-06-10 | `011-command-presentation-workflow-separation/` |\n88: \n89: > Note: `000-release-and-program-cleanup/` carries a deliberate `000` prefix (cross-cutting / program\n90: > track), so it sorts first by number but is **