{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781111570674,"sessionID":"ses_14d7be5d2ffe7zWnIxlUiw8hIZ","part":{"id":"prt_eb285c0ef0010VYeAd30GbkezQ","messageID":"msg_eb285bad8001X4XCvHP3VdeMF0","sessionID":"ses_14d7be5d2ffe7zWnIxlUiw8hIZ","snapshot":"4679972fc9b5b440ea403114c0c1d9a5450dcc48","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781111580035,"sessionID":"ses_14d7be5d2ffe7zWnIxlUiw8hIZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_x20zw9zHuMPcsow8zJxSOtkW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/009-openltm-continuity-resilience/spec.md","offset":35,"limit":45},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/009-openltm-continuity-resilience/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n39: ## 1. METADATA\n40: \n41: | Field | Value |\n42: |-------|-------|\n43: | **Level** | 1 |\n44: | **Priority** | P2 |\n45: | **Status** | Complete |\n46: | **Created** | 2026-06-08 |\n47: | **Branch** | `main` |\n48: | **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n49: | **Phase** | 9 (OpenLTM-derived, continuity/resilience) |\n50: | **Predecessor** | `008-openltm-retrieval-observability` |\n51: | **Successor** | None |\n52: | **Source** | `../research/010-openltm-memory-architecture-teachings/research.md` §8 + `sub-packet-proposals.md` (corrected Priority 4) |\n53: | **Handoff Criteria** | Defined during planning; surfaces complement (never replace) the continuity ladder. |\n54: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: <!-- ANCHOR:phase-context -->\n59: ## Phase Context\n60: \n61: OpenLTM-derived continuity phase — the **highest architectural fit** of the OpenLTM study. OpenLTM's \"document-ish\" surfaces (its bounded startup context block, its PreCompact markdown snapshot, its goal/decision/progress/gotcha facets) map naturally onto our markdown-native continuity ladder (`handover.md`, `implementation-summary.md` `_memory.continuity` frontmatter, spec-folder docs). The critical reshaping from research phase 010: OpenLTM's snapshot is a DB-derived projection (\"never the source of truth; the DB is\"); ours must instead **refresh the authored continuity docs**, which already are the source of truth.\n62: \n63: **Scope Boundary**: additive resilience surfaces over the existing session bootstrap/resume + continuity ladder. No new memory store; no row-based capture.\n64: \n65: **Dependencies**: coordinates with `005-learning-feedback-reducers` (the reshaped opt-in doc-patch capture amendment) and the existing session bootstrap/resume hooks.\n66: \n67: **Deliverables**: a bounded startup restore panel, an authored-continuity PreCompact snapshot, and a continuity-summary facet taxonomy.\n68: \n69: **Changelog**: on close, refresh the matching `../changelog/` entry using the parent packet number plus this phase folder name.\n70: <!-- /ANCHOR:phase-context -->\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n75: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n76: \n77: ### Problem Statement\n78: Our continuity ladder is richer than OpenLTM's, but it lacks a few low-tech resilience surfaces. Session restore can return unbounded results without telling the user what was *not* restored; there is no durable, plain-markdown snapshot taken before context compaction or hook-cache loss; and continuity summaries have no consistent facet shape, which makes them harder to scan and to fold proposals into.\n79: \n\n(Showing lines 35-79 of 162. Use offset=80 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 1 |\n| **Priority** | P2 |\n| **Status** | Complete |\n| **Created** | 2026-06-08 |\n| **Branch** | `main` |\n| **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n| **Phase** | 9 (OpenLTM-derived, continuity/resilience) |\n| **Predecessor** | `008-openltm-retrieval-observability` |\n| **Successor** | None |\n| **Source** | `../research/010-openltm-memory-architecture-teachings/research.md` §8 + `sub-packet-proposals.md` (corrected Priority 4) |\n| **Handoff Criteria** | Defined during planning; surfaces complement (never replace) the continuity ladder. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/009-openltm-continuity-resilience/spec.md","text":"\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 1 |\n| **Priority** | P2 |\n| **Status** | Complete |\n| **Created** | 2026-06-08 |\n| **Branch** | `main` |\n| **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n| **Phase** | 9 (OpenLTM-derived, continuity/resilience) |\n| **Predecessor** | `008-openltm-retrieval-observability` |\n| **Successor** | None |\n| **Source** | `../research/010-openltm-memory-architecture-teachings/research.md` §8 + `sub-packet-proposals.md` (corrected Priority 4) |\n| **Handoff Criteria** | Defined during planning; surfaces complement (never replace) the continuity ladder. |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phase-context -->\n## Phase Context\n\nOpenLTM-derived continuity phase — the **highest architectural fit** of the OpenLTM study. OpenLTM's \"document-ish\" surfaces (its bounded startup context block, its PreCompact markdown snapshot, its goal/decision/progress/gotcha facets) map naturally onto our markdown-native continuity ladder (`handover.md`, `implementation-summary.md` `_memory.continuity` frontmatter, spec-folder docs). The critical reshaping from research phase 010: OpenLTM's snapshot is a DB-derived projection (\"never the source of truth; the DB is\"); ours must instead **refresh the authored continuity docs**, which already are the source of truth.\n\n**Scope Boundary**: additive resilience surfaces over the existing session bootstrap/resume + continuity ladder. No new memory store; no row-based capture.\n\n**Dependencies**: coordinates with `005-learning-feedback-reducers` (the reshaped opt-in doc-patch capture amendment) and the existing session bootstrap/resume hooks.\n\n**Deliverables**: a bounded startup restore panel, an authored-continuity PreCompact snapshot, and a continuity-summary facet taxonomy.\n\n**Changelog**: on close, refresh the matching `../changelog/` entry using the parent packet number plus this phase folder name.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-context -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\nOur continuity ladder is richer than OpenLTM's, but it lacks a few low-tech resilience surfaces. Session restore can return unbounded results without telling the user what was *not* restored; there is no durable, plain-markdown snapshot taken before context compaction or hook-cache loss; and continuity summaries have no consistent facet shape, which makes them harder to scan and to fold proposals into.\n","lineStart":35,"lineEnd":79,"totalLines":162,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/009-openltm-continuity-resilience/spec.md","time":{"start":1781111580032,"end":1781111580034}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01ee24ea6aef8ed9016a299b1bfba8819186afe343cf70921f"}},"id":"prt_eb285e578001h1zSPuuGD1JAb5","sessionID":"ses_14d7be5d2ffe7zWnIxlUiw8hIZ","messageID":"msg_eb285bad8001X4XCvHP3VdeMF0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781111580077,"sessionID":"ses_14d7be5d2ffe7zWnIxlUiw8hIZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_SHF2eKoG7NFqY8t1tVyy0VTn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/000-release-cleanup/spec.md","offset":45,"limit":35},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/000-release-cleanup/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n45: \n46: # Feature Specification: 027 Release Cleanup (Phase Parent)\n47: \n48: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n49: ## 1. METADATA\n50: \n51: | Field | Value |\n52: |-------|-------|\n53: | **Level** | 2 |\n54: | **Priority** | P1 |\n55: | **Status** | Planned |\n56: | **Created** | 2026-06-10 |\n57: | **Branch** | `main` |\n58: | **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n59: | **Parent Packet** | system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement |\n60: | **Predecessor** | None |\n61: | **Successor** | 001-public-root-readme is authored last as capstone |\n62: | **Handoff Criteria** | Each child phase validates strictly and documents the outward surface it owns |\n63: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n68: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n69: \n70: ### Problem Statement\n71: The shipped 027 reality spans schema v37, default-off feature flags, new CLI front doors, constitutional rules, memory behaviors, and doctrine from peck, gem, memclaw, and openltm. Outward and governance surfaces need one coordinated phase map so documentation, catalogs, playbooks, command content, agent mirrors, and root governance describe the same current system.\n72: \n73: ### Purpose\n74: Align every outward and governance surface to the shipped 027 reality without changing source code, command router structure, agents, or skills in this scaffold. The child phases inventory the current claim, align the owned surface, and verify the result against schema v37, the new default-off flags, CLI front doors, constitutional rules, memory features, and doctrine.\n75: \n76: > **Phase-parent note:** This spec.md is the ONLY authored document at the parent level. All detailed planning, task breakdowns, and continuity live in the child phase folders listed in the Phase Documentation Map below.\n77: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n78: \n79: ---\n\n(Showing lines 45-79 of 165. Use offset=80 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n# Feature Specification: 027 Release Cleanup (Phase Parent)\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 2 |\n| **Priority** | P1 |\n| **Status** | Planned |\n| **Created** | 2026-06-10 |\n| **Branch** | `main` |\n| **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n| **Parent Packet** | system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement |\n| **Predecessor** | None |\n| **Successor** | 001-public-root-readme is authored last as capstone |\n| **Handoff Criteria** | Each child phase validates strictly and documents the outward surface it owns |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/000-release-cleanup/spec.md","text":"\n# Feature Specification: 027 Release Cleanup (Phase Parent)\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 2 |\n| **Priority** | P1 |\n| **Status** | Planned |\n| **Created** | 2026-06-10 |\n| **Branch** | `main` |\n| **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n| **Parent Packet** | system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement |\n| **Predecessor** | None |\n| **Successor** | 001-public-root-readme is authored last as capstone |\n| **Handoff Criteria** | Each child phase validates strictly and documents the outward surface it owns |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\nThe shipped 027 reality spans schema v37, default-off feature flags, new CLI front doors, constitutional rules, memory behaviors, and doctrine from peck, gem, memclaw, and openltm. Outward and governance surfaces need one coordinated phase map so documentation, catalogs, playbooks, command content, agent mirrors, and root governance describe the same current system.\n\n### Purpose\nAlign every outward and governance surface to the shipped 027 reality without changing source code, command router structure, agents, or skills in this scaffold. The child phases inventory the current claim, align the owned surface, and verify the result against schema v37, the new default-off flags, CLI front doors, constitutional rules, memory features, and doctrine.\n\n> **Phase-parent note:** This spec.md is the ONLY authored document at the parent level. All detailed planning, task breakdowns, and continuity live in the child phase folders listed in the Phase Documentation Map below.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---","lineStart":45,"lineEnd":79,"totalLines":165,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/000-release-cleanup/spec.md","time":{"start":1781111580062,"end":1781111580076}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01ee24ea6aef8ed9016a299b1bfbbc8191bc20569aa74e94e9"}},"id":"prt_eb285e59b001gHmsyMEp2958C7","sessionID":"ses_14d7be5d2ffe7zWnIxlUiw8hIZ","messageID":"msg_eb285bad8001X4XCvHP3VdeMF0"}}
